(26, 2, 'Date: February 9, 2026\n\n1. Project Updates\nProject Name: simple Marketing GmbH & Co KG (Manuel R. (.simple Marketing GmbH & Co KG) (Contract ID: 42092892)- Moninder Kaur)\nDesign/Preview Link: https://Stagingdev34.rechteasy.at \nWork Completed:\n- search console issue (in this site there are various search console issues after consulting with maninder sir and ashish sir lets start working on that issue)\n- start working on chess game issues issues (start working on chess issues chess game issue which is integrated in the wordpres ssite\nhttps://client1.karan.devprojects.in/ username pass chess developed one staging site and installed one plugin and work on the functionality of all plugin how this plugin work andin next working day lets start the functionality part of that plugin and gunctionality of that plugin mentioned given below I. How to Use the Plugin on Your Site\nTo use the plugin, you simply need to create WordPress pages and paste the following shortcodes:\nConnection Page ([cc_connect]):\nPurpose: This is where you (or your students) link Chess.com/Lichess usernames.\nActions: Users can create a \"Player\" profile and add multiple accounts. It also allows you to set up a \"Coach Profile\" (name, bio, logo) for reports.\nGames List ([cc_games]):\nPurpose: A searchable dashboard of all imported games.\nFeatures: Filter by date, opening, result, or color. It shows high-level stats like win rates and rating progress.\nGame Detail ([cc_game]):\nPurpose: The main analysis board.\nFeatures: An interactive chessboard with move navigation, engine analysis (Stockfish), Lichess opening explorer, and a \"Notes\" section for coach-student feedback.\nCoaching Dashboard ([cc_coaching]):\nPurpose: A summarized view for the coach to see which games need review based on AI-flagged \"Turning Points\" or large blunders.\nPuzzles ([cc_puzzles]):\nPurpose: Displays chess puzzles.\nFeatures: Can recommend puzzles based on the openings the user actually plays in their real games.\nHeader Settings ([ccwp_header_prefs]):\nPurpose: A small settings gear (usually placed in a header or sidebar) to let users change piece styles (Classic, Neo, Alpha) and board colors.\nII. Setup & Admin Configuration\nBefore the plugin works fully, you must configure it in the WordPress Admin -> Chess Coach WP menu:\nAPI Keys: You need an OpenAI API Key if you want the \"AI Coaching\" feature (which writes summaries of games) to work.\nOpenings Catalog: Go to the \"Openings\" tab and click \"Import openings catalog\". This populates the database with thousands of opening names so the plugin can recognize them in your games.\nPuzzles: If you want the puzzle feature, you must provide a URL to a Lichess Puzzle CSV dump (as the file is too large to include in the plugin).\nIII. How it Works (The Technical Logic)\nThe plugin follows a specific \"Analysis Pipeline\" to ensure your site stays fast:\nThe Job Queue (The \"Runner\"):\nWhen you click \"Import,\" the plugin doesn\'t download the games immediately (which would crash the page). Instead, it adds a Job to a background queue.\nA background process (WP-Cron) runs every few minutes to process these jobs.\nImport Logic:\nIt fetches \"Archives\" from Chess.com/Lichess.\nIt saves games into custom database tables (wp_ccwp_games) for fast searching.\nAnalysis Pipeline:\nStage 1 (Opening): It looks at the PGN and matches it against the Openings Catalog to identify the name (e.g., \"Sicilian Defense: Najdorf Variation\").\nStage 2 (Engine): It sends the game to an external engine API to calculate Centipawn Loss (ACPL) and identify blunders/mistakes.\nStage 3 (AI): It sends the engine data and PGN to OpenAI. The AI acts as a \"Coach,\" writing a human-readable summary of what the player did wrong and what they should practice.\nThe UI Layer:\nThe chessboard uses Chess.js for logic and custom SVG assets for pieces.\nIt uses Lichess Cloud Eval for the real-time engine on the \"Game Detail\" page, so you don\'t have to run a heavy engine on your own server.\nSummary of Benefits\nScalable: It uses its own DB tables, so it can handle thousands of games without slowing down WordPress.\nMulti-User: Different WordPress users see only their own games.\nCoach-Centric: It\'s designed for a coach to manage multiple students (Players) from one interface.)\nWork Pending: [Please fill]\n\n2. Tracker Status\nTotal Tracker: [Please fill]\nRunning Tracker: [Please fill]\nPending Tracker: [Please fill]\n\n3. System Details\nSystem Seat Number: [Please fill]\nSystem Password: [Please fill]\nTracker Tabs Open: [Yes/No]\n\n4. Client Communication\n[Any updates/Message for client]\n\n5. Message for BD Team\n[Follow-up requirements]\n', '<p>Hello Team,</p>\n\n<p>Please find below the End-of-Day (EOD) report for today, October 26, 2023.</p>\n\n<h3>1. Project Updates</h3>\n\n<h4>Project: simple Marketing GmbH &amp; Co KG (Contract ID: 42092892 - Moninder Kaur)</h4>\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>Page/Task Name:</strong> Search Console Issues Investigation</li>\n    <li><strong>Design/Preview Link:</strong> <a href=\"https://Stagingdev34.rechteasy.at\">https://Stagingdev34.rechteasy.at</a></li>\n    <li><strong>Work Completed:</strong>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Initiated an investigation into various search console issues identified on the staging site.</li>\n            <li>Conducted a consultation with Moninder Sir and Ashish Sir to understand the scope and plan the approach for resolving these issues.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li><strong>Work Pending:</strong> Further analysis and implementation of solutions for the identified search console issues.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4>Project: WordPress Chess Game Plugin Integration (Client 1)</h4>\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>Page/Task Name:</strong> Chess Coach WP Plugin Setup and Research</li>\n    <li><strong>Design/Preview Link:</strong> <a href=\"https://client1.karan.devprojects.in/\">https://client1.karan.devprojects.in/</a></li>\n    <li><strong>Work Completed:</strong>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Set up a dedicated staging environment for the chess game integration project.</li>\n            <li>Successfully installed and performed initial configuration of the Chess Coach WP plugin.</li>\n            <li>Conducted a thorough review to understand the plugin\'s core functionalities, including its various shortcodes (e.g., Connection Page, Games List, Game Detail, Coaching Dashboard, Puzzles, Header Settings).</li>\n            <li>Analyzed the administrative setup requirements, such as API key integration (OpenAI), openings catalog import, and Lichess Puzzle CSV configuration.</li>\n            <li>Reviewed the plugin\'s underlying technical logic and analysis pipeline, covering the job queue, import process, and multi-stage analysis (Opening, Engine, AI).</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n    <li><strong>Work Pending:</strong> Commencing the implementation and full integration of the Chess Coach WP plugin\'s functionalities based on the comprehensive research conducted today.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>2. Tracker Status</h3>\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>Total Tracker:</strong> [Please fill Total Tracker Hours]</li>\n    <li><strong>Running Tracker:</strong> [Please fill Running Tracker Hours]</li>\n    <li><strong>Pending Tracker:</strong> [Please fill Pending Tracker Hours]</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>3. System Details (Where the tracker was used)</h3>\n<ul>\n    <li><strong>System Seat Number:</strong> [Please fill Seat No.]</li>\n    <li><strong>System Password:</strong> [Please fill Password]</li>\n    <li><strong>Tracker Tabs Open:</strong> [Yes/No]</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>4. Client Communication</h3>\n<p>[Any updates or messages for the client will be added here, if applicable.]</p>\n\n<h3>5. Message for BD Team</h3>\n<p>[Follow-up requirements for the Night Shift will be added here, if applicable.]</p>\n\n<p>Thank you for your attention.</p>\n\n<p><em>Note: This report is generated based on available information and approximates c