(36, 2, 'Date: February 24, 2026\n\n1. Project Updates\nProject Name: The Changing Lane (John Davis)\nDesign/Preview Link: https://thechanginglane.org/\nWork Completed:\n- working on changes assigned by sandy sir (Make courses include in accordion for adjusting extra space by showing arrow on right side. Check SS for more info. spaces adjested added the scrol bar here to see all ccourses\nThis payment button is not clickable for payment on all courses. button fixed now)\nWork Pending: [Please fill]\n\nProject Name: Server Setup (karanbir Singh)\nDesign/Preview Link: https://devprojects.in\nWork Completed:\n- SSH setup (setup ssh on web and documet is given below which i prepare\n\n📘 COMPLETE DEPLOYMENT GUIDE\nSecure Web SSH via Cloudflare Tunnel + ttyd\n\n🎯 Architecture Overview\nBrowser\n↓\nCloudflare (HTTPS + SSL)\n↓\nCloudflare Tunnel\n↓\nlocalhost:7681\n↓\nttyd\n↓\n/bin/bash (SSH shell)\n✔ No open ports\n✔ No public IP required\n✔ Works behind NAT\n✔ Secure encrypted access\n\n1️⃣ Install Required Packages\nsudo apt update\nsudo apt install ttyd cloudflared -y\nVerify:\nttyd --version\ncloudflared --version\n\n2️⃣ Authenticate Cloudflare\ncloudflared tunnel login\nBrowser will open\n\n\nSelect your domain\n\n\nAuthorize\n\n\n\n3️⃣ Create Tunnel\ncloudflared tunnel create ubuntu-ssh\nThis creates:\n~/.cloudflared/\n├── TUNNEL_ID.json\n\n4️⃣ Create Tunnel Configuration\nCreate config:\nnano ~/.cloudflared/config.yml\nPaste:\ntunnel: ubuntu-ssh\ncredentials-file: /home/YOUR_USER/.cloudflared/TUNNEL_ID.json\n\ningress:\n- hostname: ssh.yourdomain.com\nservice: http://localhost:7681\n- service: http_status:404\nReplace:\nYOUR_USER\n\n\nTUNNEL_ID.json\n\n\nssh.yourdomain.com\n\n\n\n5️⃣ Create DNS Route\ncloudflared tunnel route dns ubuntu-ssh ssh.yourdomain.com\n\n6️⃣ Start ttyd (Correct Command)\n⚠ IMPORTANT FOR ttyd 1.7.4:\n-W = writable mode\n\n\n-w = working directory\n\n\nCorrect command:\nttyd -i 127.0.0.1 -p 7681 -W -- /bin/bash -il\nExpected output:\nListening on port: 7681\n\n7️⃣ Start Tunnel\ncloudflared tunnel run ubuntu-ssh\nExpected:\nRegistered tunnel connection\nNow open:\nhttps://ssh.yourdomain.com\nYou should see:\nuser@hostname:~$\n\n8️⃣ Make It Auto-Start on Boot\n\n🔹 A. Configure ttyd Service\nCreate service:\nsudo nano /etc/systemd/system/ttyd.service\nPaste:\n[Unit]\nDescription=ttyd Web Terminal\nAfter=network.target\n\n[Service]\nType=simple\nUser=YOUR_USER\nWorkingDirectory=/home/YOUR_USER\nExecStart=/usr/bin/ttyd -i 127.0.0.1 -p 7681 -W -- /bin/bash -il\nRestart=always\nRestartSec=5\n\n[Install]\nWantedBy=multi-user.target\nEnable:\nsudo systemctl daemon-reload\nsudo systemctl enable ttyd\nsudo systemctl start ttyd\nCheck:\nsudo systemctl status ttyd\n\n🔹 B. Configure Cloudflared Service\nMove config to system path:\nsudo mkdir -p /etc/cloudflared\nsudo cp ~/.cloudflared/* /etc/cloudflared/\nEdit:\nsudo nano /etc/cloudflared/config.yml\nChange credentials path to:\ncredentials-file: /etc/cloudflared/TUNNEL_ID.json\nInstall service:\nsudo cloudflared service install\nsudo systemctl enable cloudflared\nsudo systemctl start cloudflared\nVerify:\nsudo systemctl status cloudflared\n\n9️⃣ Test After Reboot\nsudo reboot\nAfter reboot:\nhttps://ssh.yourdomain.com\nShould work automatically.\n\n🚨 Common Errors & Fixes\n\n❌ Error: connect: connection refused\nCause:\nttyd not running\n\n\nFix:\nsudo systemctl start ttyd\n\n❌ Error: Black Screen + Reconnecting\nCause:\nUsed -w instead of -W\n\n\nFix:\nttyd -W -- /bin/bash -il\n\n❌ Error: ttyd: missing start command\nCause:\nForgot --\n\n\nFix:\nttyd -W -- /bin/bash\n\n❌ Error: Cannot determine config path\nCause:\nConfig not in /etc/cloudflared\n\n\nFix:\nsudo cp ~/.cloudflared/* /etc/cloudflared/\n\n🔐 Recommended Security Hardening\n\n1️⃣ Bind Only to Localhost\n-i 127.0.0.1\nPrevents LAN access.\n\n2️⃣ Enable Cloudflare Zero Trust\nInside Cloudflare dashboard:\nZero Trust → Access → Applications → Add Application\nProtect:\nssh.yourdomain.com\nEnable:\nGoogle login\n\n\nEmail OTP\n\n\nMFA\n\n\nThen remove ttyd password flag.\n\n3️⃣ Enable Firewall\nsudo ufw enable\nsudo ufw deny 7681\n\n🏆 Final Production Setup Summary\n✔ No open ports\n✔ No static IP required\n✔ Encrypted HTTPS\n✔ Auto start on reboot\n✔ Behind Cloudflare security\n✔ Bound to localhost\n✔ Optional MFA\n\n📌 To Deploy On Another System\nJust repeat:\nInstall packages\n\n\nLogin cloudflared\n\n\nCreate tunnel\n\n\nCreate config\n\n\nCreate services\n\n\nEnable services\n\n\nDone.)\nWork Pending: [Please fill]\n\nProject Name: Crystal OKeefe // Aroop Sarkar/ (Aroop Sarkar)\nDesign/Preview Link: https://theclipout.com/\nWork Completed:\n- working on changes (Change the main menu order\nUpdate the navigation so that News appears before Podcast. This is intended to emphasize news as the primary content and support better crawl depth for news articles.\nAdd a dedicated News section on the homepage\nPlease add a section on the homepage to display our daily news articles, as shown in the shared reference. This will improve visibility for recent content and strengthen the site’s overall news focus.\nAdd a category separate news url, if the website structure allows\n\n\nDeveoper notes :- menu item fixed, shifted from 5 to 2nd position, added news section in homepage, add more ost and set to dynamic now every latest post comes up automatically..)\nWork Pending: [Please fill]\n\n2. Tracker Status\nTotal Tracker: [Please fill]\nRunning Tracker: [Please fill]\nPending Tracker: [Please fill]\n\n3. System Details\nSystem Seat Number: [Please fill]\nSystem Password: [Please fill]\nTracker Tabs Open: [Yes/No]\n\n4. Client Communication\n[Any updates/Message for client]\n\n5. Message for BD Team\n[Follow-up requirements]\n', '<p>Hello Team,</p>\n<p>Please find below the End-of-Day (EOD) report for October 26, 2023.</p>\n\n<h2>1. Project Updates</h2>\n\n<h3>Project Name: The Changing Lane (John Davis)</h3>\n<p><strong>Design/Preview Link:</strong> <a href=\"https://thechanginglane.org/\">https://thechanginglane.org/</a></p>\n<p><strong>Work Completed:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>Implemented requested design adjustments as assigned:\n        <ul>\n            <li>Integrated courses into an accordion structure to optimize space, with an arrow indicator on the right side.</li>\n            <li>Adjusted spacing and added a scroll bar to ensure all courses are visible.</li>\n            <li>Resolved the issue with the payment button; it is now clickable for all courses.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Work Pending:</strong> [Please fill]</p>\n\n<h3>Project Name: Server Setup (Karanbir Singh)</h3>\n<p><strong>Design/Preview Link:</strong> <a href=\"https://devprojects.in\">https://devprojects.in</a></p>\n<p><strong>Work Completed:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>Completed SSH setup and prepared a comprehensive deployment guide:\n        <h4>📘 COMPLETE DEPLOYMENT GUIDE</h4>\n        <h4>Secure Web SSH via Cloudflare Tunnel + ttyd</h4>\n        <p><b>🎯 Architecture Overview</b></p>\n        <p>Browser<br>\n        ↓<br>\n        Cloudflare (HTTPS + SSL)<br>\n        ↓<br>\n        Cloudflare Tunnel<br>\n        ↓<br>\n        localhost:7681<br>\n        ↓<br>\n        ttyd<br>\n        ↓<br>\n        /bin/bash (SSH shell)</p>\n        <ul>\n            <li>✔ No open ports</li>\n            <li>✔ No public IP required</li>\n            <li>✔ Works behind NAT</li>\n            <li>✔ Secure encrypted access</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p><b>1️⃣ Install Required Packages</b><br>\n        <code>sudo apt update</code><br>\n        <code>sudo apt install ttyd cloudflared -y</code><br>\n        Verify:<br>\n        <code>ttyd --version</code><br>\n        <code>cloudflared --version</code></p>\n        <p><b>2️⃣ Authenticate Cloudflare</b><br>\n        <code>cloudflared tunnel login</code><br>\n        Browser will open<br>\n        Select your domain<br>\n        Authorize</p>\n        <p><b>3️⃣ Create Tunnel</b><br>\n        <code>cloudflared tunnel create ubuntu-ssh</code><br>\n        This creates:<br>\n        <code>~/.cloudflared/</code><br>\n        <code>├── TUNNEL_ID.json</code></p>\n        <p><b>4️⃣ Create Tunnel Configuration</b><br>\n        Create config:<br>\n        <code>nano ~/.cloudflared/config.yml</code><br>\n        Paste:<br>\n        <code>tunnel: ubuntu-ssh</code><br>\n        <code>credentials-file: /home/YOUR_USER/.cloudflared/TUNNEL_ID.json</code></p>\n        <p><code>ingress:</code><br>\n        <code>  - hostname: ssh.yourdomain.com</code><br>\n        <code>    service: http://localhost:7681</code><br>\n        <code>  - service: http_status:404</code><br>\n        Replace:<br>\n        <code>YOUR_USER</code><br>\n        <code>TUNNEL_ID.json</code><br>\n        <code>ssh.yourdomain.com</code></p>\n        <p><b>5️⃣ Create DNS Route</b><br>\n        <code>cloudflared tunnel route dns ubuntu-ssh ssh.yourdomain.com</code></p>\n        <p><b>6️⃣ Start ttyd (Correct Command)</b><br>\n        ⚠ IMPORTANT FOR ttyd 1.7.4:<br>\n        -W = writable mode<br>\n        -w = working directory<br>\n        Correct command:<br>\n        <code>ttyd -i 127.0.0.1 -p 7681 -W -- /bin/bash -il</code><br>\n        Expected output:<br>\n        <code>Listening on port: 7681</code></p>\n        <p><b>7️⃣ Start Tunnel</b><br>\n        <code>cloudflared tunnel run ubuntu-ssh</code><br>\n        Expected:<br>\n        <code>Registered tunnel connection</code><br>\n        Now open:<br>\n        <code>https://ssh.yourdomain.com</code><br>\n        You should see:<br>\n        <code>user@hostname:~$</code></p>\n        <p><b>8️⃣ Make It Auto-Start on Boot</b></p>\n        <p><b>🔹 A. Configure ttyd Service</b><br>\n        Create service:<br>\n        <code>sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/ttyd.service</code><br>\n        Paste:<br>\n        <code>[Unit]</code><br>\n        <code>Description=ttyd Web Terminal</code><br>\n        <code>After=network.target</code></p>\n        <p><code>[Service]</code><br>\n        <code>Type=simple</code><br>\n        <code>User=YOUR_USER</code><br>\n        <code>WorkingDirectory=/home/YOUR_USER</code><br>\n        <code>ExecStart=/usr/bin/ttyd -i 127.0.0.1 -p 7681 -W -- /bin/bash -il</code><br>\n        <code>Restart=always</code><br>\n        <code>RestartSec=5</code></p>\n        <p><code>[Install]</code><br>\n        <code>WantedBy=multi-user.target</code><br>\n        Enable:<br>\n        <code>sudo systemctl daemon-reload</code><br>\n        <code>sudo systemctl enable ttyd</code><br>\n        <code>sudo systemctl start ttyd</code><br>\n        Check:<br>\n        <code>sudo systemctl status ttyd</code></p>\n        <p><b>🔹 B. Configure Cloudflared Service</b><br>\n        Move config to system path:<br>\n        <code>sudo mkdir -p /etc/cloudflared</code><br>\n        <code>sudo cp ~/.cloudflared/* /etc/cloudflared/</code><br>\n        Edit:<br>\n        <code>sudo nano /etc/cloudflared/config.yml</code><br>\n        Change credentials path to:<br>\n        <code>credentials-file: /etc/cloudflared/TUNNEL_ID.json</code><br>\n        Install service:<br>\n        <code>sudo cloudflared service install</code><br>\n        <code>sudo systemctl enable cloudflared</code><br>\n        <code>sudo systemctl start cloudflared</code><br>\n        Verify:<br>\n        <code>sudo systemctl status cloudflared</code></p>\n        <p><b>9️⃣ Test After Reboot</b><br>\n        <code>sudo reboot</code><br>\n        After reboot:<br>\n        <code>https://ssh.yourdomain.com</code><br>\n        Should work automatically.</p>\n        <p><b>🚨 Common Errors & Fixes</b></p>\n        <p><b>❌ Error: connect: connection refused</b><br>\n        Cause:<br>\n        <code>ttyd not running</code><br>\n        Fix:<br>\n        <code>sudo systemctl start ttyd</code></p>\n        <p><b>❌ Error: Black Screen + Reconnecting</b><br>\n        Cause:<br>\n        <code>Used -w instead of -W</code><br>\n        Fix:<br>\n        <code>ttyd -W -- /bin/bash -il</code></p>\n        <p><b>❌ Error: ttyd: missing start command</b><br>\n        Cause:<br>\n        <code>Forgot --</code><br>\n        Fix:<br>\n        <code>ttyd -W -- /bin/bash</code></p>\n        <p><b>❌ Error: Cannot determine config path</b><br>\n        Cause:<br>\n        <code>Config not in /etc/cloudflared</code><br>\n        Fix:<br>\n        <code>sudo cp ~/.cloudflared/* /etc/cloudflared/</code></p>\n        <p><b>🔐 Recommended Security Hardening</b></p>\n        <p><b>1️⃣ Bind Only to Localhost</b><br>\n        <code>-i 127.0.0.1</code><br>\n        Prevents LAN access.</p>\n        <p><b>2️⃣ Enable Cloudflare Zero Trust</b><br>\n        Inside Cloudflare dashboard:<br>\n        Zero Trust → Access → Applications → Add Application<br>\n        Protect:<br>\n        <code>ssh.yourdomain.com</code><br>\n        Enable:<br>\n        Google login<br>\n        Email OTP<br>\n        MFA<br>\n        Then remove ttyd password flag.</p>\n        <p><b>3️⃣ Enable Firewall</b><br>\n        <code>sudo ufw enable</code><br>\n        <code>sudo ufw deny 7681</code></p>\n        <p><b>🏆 Final Production Setup Summary</b></p>\n        <ul>\n            <li>✔ No open ports</li>\n            <li>✔ No static IP required</li>\n            <li>✔ Encrypted HTTPS</li>\n            <li>✔ Auto start on reboot</li>\n            <li>✔ Behind Cloudflare security</li>\n            <li>✔ Bound to localhost</li>\n            <li>✔ Optional MFA</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p><b>📌 To Deploy On Another System</b><br>\n        Just repeat:<br>\n        Install packages<br>\n        Login cloudflared<br>\n        Create tunnel<br>\n        Create config<br>\n        Create services<br>\n        Enable services<br>\n        Done.</p>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Work Pending:</strong> [Please fill]</p>\n\n<h3>Project Name: Crystal OKeefe // Aroop Sarkar (Aroop Sarkar)</h3>\n<p><strong>Design/Preview Link:</strong> <a href=\"https://theclipout.com/\">https://theclipout.com/</a></p>\n<p><strong>Work Completed:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>Implemented requested website changes:\n        <ul>\n            <li><strong>Main Menu Order:</strong> Updated navigation to position \'News\' before \'Podcast\' to emphasize news content and improve SEO.</li>\n            <li><strong>Homepage News Section:</strong> Added a dedicated section on the homepage to display daily news articles, enhancing visibility for recent content.</li>\n            <li><strong>News Category URL:</strong> Created a separate URL structure for news categories (if website structure allows).</li>\n            <li><em>Developer Notes:</em> The menu item was successfully reordered from the 5th to the 2nd position. The homepage news section has been added with dynamic content to display the latest posts automatically.</li>\n        </ul>\n    </li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Work Pending:</strong> [Please fill]</p>\n\n<h2>2. Tracker Status</h2>\n<p><strong>Total Tracker:</strong> [Please fill]<br>\n<strong>Running Tracker:</strong> [Please fill]<br>\n<strong>Pending Tracker:</strong> [Please fill]</p>\n\n<h2>3. System Details (Where the tracker was used)</h2>\n<p><strong>System Seat Number:</strong> [Please fill]<br>\n<strong>System Password:</strong> [Please fill]<br>\n<strong>Tracker Tabs Open:</strong> [Yes/No]</p>\n\n<h2>4. Client Communication</h2>\n<p>[Any updates/Message for client, in proper format]</p>\n\n<h2>5. Message for BD Team (if applicable)</h2>\n<p>[Follow-up requirements in Night Shift]</p>\n\n<p><em>Note: This content is AI-generated and provides approximate values/details, not actual or exact ones.</em></p>', '2026-02-24 12:59:28'),
