(727, 2, 'Affiliate Program Workflow 1. Registering a User •	Log in to your WordPress Admin Panel. •	Navigate to: Users > Add New URL: https://getmusclecare.com/wp-admin/user-new.php •	While adding a new user, you can check “Add the user as an affiliate”. o	If checked, the user will automatically be registered as an affiliate in AffiliateWP. o	Otherwise, you can manually register them later in AffiliateWP > Affiliates > Add New. URL: https://getmusclecare.com/wp-admin/admin.php?page=affiliate-wp-affiliates ________________________________________ 2. Setting Affiliate Commission Rates •	Go to AffiliateWP > Affiliates. •	Click on the affiliate’s name to open their profile. •	Locate the Referral Rate field. •	Enter the percentage value (e.g., 15 or 20). o	You only need to enter the number; AffiliateWP will automatically add the % symbol. ________________________________________ 3. Generating Affiliate Links •	Go to Affiliate Control > Link Generator in WP-Admin. •	Select the affiliate (e.g., Test User 1). •	Choose the page or product you want to generate the referral link for. •	Copy the generated URL and share it with friends, customers, or on social media. ________________________________________ 4. Tracking Referrals •	When someone purchases through an affiliate’s link, the referral commission will appear in your dashboard. •	To view: AffiliateWP > Referrals URL: https://getmusclecare.com/wp-admin/admin.php?page=affiliate-wp-referrals ________________________________________ With these steps, you can register affiliates, set their commission percentage, generate custom referral links, and track earnings in AffiliateWP.', '2025-09-24 18:19:01', '2025-09-24 19:34:46', '2025-09-24', '2025-09-24 12:49:01', NULL, NULL),
