(1029, 2, 'start working on project assigned by sandy sir with given below description  Everything is coming together nicely. The video page looks good. I want to position this as a How To section for how to do basic weaving things. As I review everything, I have some further ideas. Let me know what you think.   Home Page  1. Should photo/words “Welcome to Weavelry” you see immediately be smaller so that people know that there is more to scroll underneath? And can that photo be brighter?  2. I can work on what appears underneath; not sure we need too much.  New Page  1. We need another page called “Patterns,” because while people want to share their work in Share Projects, most people want to find exact patterns.  2. I would like it to appear before Share Projects in the top menu. You can put About Us on the end, right hand side. I would like people to be able to upload a document (the pattern), or add a URL that links to a pattern, or add a url that links to being able to buy a pattern. All of these docs or urls would be from the user.  3. Here’s some text: Share patterns here. You may upload a document with your original pattern or a link to a free pattern or a link to purchase a pattern. Note: all uploads must follow copyright rules. If you are not sure, ask.  4. This can be similar to the share projects page (but everything is public)  Questions/Answers Page  1. Change this to Your Weaving Questions  2. Change this text: Ask a specific question to solve your weaving problem. All responses are generated from the group, by the group and for the group.  Rules and FAQ:  At some point, I need to write the posting rules and create a FAQ page. Any suggestions on where to put those?  Contact Page:  Eventually, I will need an info.weavery email. The contact page should have two options. Report a problem. And Contact.', '2025-12-26 09:51:04', '2025-12-26 18:17:19', '2025-12-26', '2025-12-26 04:21:04', NULL, NULL),
